https://codeforces.com/problemset/problem/855/B

Value of x is calculated as maximum of p·ai + q·aj + r·ak for given p, q, r and array a1, a2, ... an such that 1 ≤ i ≤ j ≤ k ≤ n. Help Snape find the value of x. Do note that the value of x may be negative.

Input
First line of input contains 4 integers n, p, q, r ( - 109 ≤ p, q, r ≤ 109, 1 ≤ n ≤ 105).

Next line of input contains n space separated integers a1, a2, ... an ( - 109 ≤ ai ≤ 109).

1)All PQR are positive 
    take max_element from array and multiply with PQR (max_element*P+max_element*Q+max_element*R)
2)else if negative element are present in PQR 
          negative(PQR)*min_element||negative(PQR)*min_element
          + Positive(PQR)*max_element||Positive(PQR)*max_element
          + Positive(PQR)*max_element||Positive(PQR)*max_element
          
 class MaximizeExpression
{
	public int calculateMaximumExpression(int PQR[],int arr[])
	{
		int max_expression = 0;
		int countNegative  = countTotalNegativeElementPQR(PQR);
		int negativePQR[] = new int[countNegative];
		int positivePQR[] = new int[PQR.length-countNegative];
		int minElement = getMin(arr);
		int maxElement = getMAx(arr);
		for(int i =0 ;i<negativePQR.length;i++)
		{
			max_expression = max_expression + negativePQR[i]*minElement;
		}
		for(int i  = 0 ;i<positivePQR.length;i++)
		{
			max_expression = max_expression + positivePQR[i]*max_expression;
		}
		return max_expression;
		
	}

	private int getMAx(int[] arr) {
		int max = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
		for(int i = 0;i<arr.length;i++)
		{
			if(max<arr[i])
				max = arr[i];
		}
		return max;
	}

	private int getMin(int[] arr) {
		int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
		for(int  i = 0 ;i<arr.length;i++)
		{
			if(min>arr[i])
				min = arr[i];
		}
		return min;
	}

	private int countTotalNegativeElementPQR(int[] pQR) {
		int c = 0 ;
		for(int  i =0;i<pQR.length;i++)
		{
			if(pQR[i]<0)
				c=c+1;
		}
		return 0;
	}
}
         
          
